# {{ project_name }}

Odoo {{ odoo_version }} development environment powered by Nix flakes
(Python {{ python_version }}, PostgreSQL {{ postgres_version }}).
Generated from [nixodoo-copier-template](https://github.com/okolovmark/nixodoo-copier-template).

## Quick start

```bash
# 1. Generate .env (ports, DB credentials — defaults are fine)
nix run .#create-env

# 2. Clone Odoo {{ odoo_version }} + addon repos, build the addons symlink farm
nix run .#update-repos

# 3. Import Odoo's python requirements into pyproject.toml and lock them
nix run .#bootstrap-deps

# 4. Install the dev toolchain (odoo, psql, ruff, uv, ...) into your profile
nix profile add .#dev-server

# 5. Local postgres cluster + odoo.conf + nginx.conf + systemd user services
nix run .#setup-dev

# 6. Start everything
systemctl --user enable --now postgres.service odoo.service nginx.service odoo-logrotate.timer

# Odoo is now at http://localhost:{{ nginx_port }}
```

`welcome-message` prints ports, versions and useful commands at any time.

## Commands

| Command | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `nix run .#create-env` | interactive `.env` generator |
| `nix run .#update-repos` | clone/update `repos.yaml` + `addons.yaml`, rebuild the addons farm |
| `nix run .#bootstrap-deps` | import `src/odoo/requirements.txt` into `pyproject.toml` + `uv lock` |
| `nix run .#create-odoo-config` | generate `odoo.conf` (random `admin_passwd`) |
| `nix run .#create-nginx-config` | generate `.nginx/nginx.conf` |
| `nix run .#create-systemd-service` | systemd user units (odoo, nginx, log rotation) |
| `nix run .#setup-postgres` | init the project-local PostgreSQL cluster + unit |
{% if backup_s3_bucket %}
| `nix run .#download-backup` | fetch the latest prod dump from S3, restore + neutralize |
| `nix run .#create-aws-config` | interactive `.aws/credentials` generator |
{% endif %}
{% if prod_ssh_host %}
| `nix run .#setup-ssh-access` | one-time SSH key + config for the remote servers |
{% endif %}
| `nix run .#setup-dev` | everything above in one go |
| `nix flake check` | shellcheck over all project scripts |

## Daily use

```bash
# Update/install a module (stop odoo.service first)
odoo -c ${{ project_dir_var }}/odoo.conf -u module_name --workers 0 --stop-after-init --logfile=/dev/stdout

# Interactive shell
odoo shell -c ${{ project_dir_var }}/odoo.conf --workers 0 --stop-after-init

# Logs
journalctl --user -u odoo.service -f | ccze -A
```

{% if backup_s3_bucket %}
## Production backups

`nix run .#download-backup` restores the latest dump from `s3://{{ backup_s3_bucket }}`
into `$PGDATABASE` (or a name passed as the first argument), then sanitizes it:
Odoo's native neutralization (`odoo neutralize` — every installed module's
`data/neutralize.sql`) plus `nix/scripts/dev-fixup.sql` (local `admin`/`admin`
login, requeue stuck queue jobs). Restore errors land in `backup/pg_restore.log`.

{% endif %}
